---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-network-matters', text: 'Why Network Size Matters', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Network Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-by-region', text: 'Networks by Region', level: 2 },
  { id: 'direct-billing', text: 'Direct Billing Networks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Direct Billing Insurance', href: '/best/direct-billing-insurance' },
  { title: 'Premium Insurance', href: '/best/premium-insurance' },
  { title: 'Worldwide Insurance', href: '/best/worldwide-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'globalNetwork', header: 'Global Network' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Hospital Partners' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
  { key: 'strength', header: 'Network Strength' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', globalNetwork: '1.5M+ providers', hospitals: '39,000+ hospitals', directBilling: 'Extensive', strength: 'Excellent globally' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', globalNetwork: '1.2M+ providers', hospitals: '35,000+ hospitals', directBilling: 'Extensive', strength: 'Excellent globally' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', globalNetwork: '1M+ providers', hospitals: '30,000+ hospitals', directBilling: 'Strong US', strength: 'Best in US' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', globalNetwork: '800K+ providers', hospitals: '25,000+ hospitals', directBilling: 'Good', strength: 'Strong in Europe' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', globalNetwork: '500K+ providers', hospitals: '20,000+ hospitals', directBilling: 'Limited', strength: 'Moderate' },
];

const regionColumns = [
  { key: 'region', header: 'Region' },
  { key: 'bestNetwork', header: 'Best Network' },
  { key: 'runnerUp', header: 'Runner-Up' },
  { key: 'notes', header: 'Notes' },
];

const regionRows = [
  { region: 'North America', bestNetwork: 'Aetna', runnerUp: 'Cigna', notes: 'Aetna has deepest US network' },
  { region: 'Europe', bestNetwork: 'Allianz Care', runnerUp: 'Cigna', notes: 'Allianz European heritage' },
  { region: 'Asia Pacific', bestNetwork: 'Cigna', runnerUp: 'Bupa', notes: 'Both excellent in Asia' },
  { region: 'Middle East', bestNetwork: 'Cigna', runnerUp: 'Bupa', notes: 'Strong Gulf presence' },
  { region: 'Latin America', bestNetwork: 'Cigna', runnerUp: 'IMG', notes: 'Cigna leads in LATAM' },
  { region: 'Africa', bestNetwork: 'Cigna', runnerUp: 'Bupa', notes: 'Limited networks overall' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="5 Best Expat Insurance Plans by Network Size (2026 Compared)"
  description="Compare 5 insurers by hospital network size—up to 1.5M+ providers and 39,000+ hospitals. Direct billing coverage by region."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance for Provider Networks"
  subheadline="A large provider network means more choices, easier direct billing, and better access to quality care. Here are the insurers with the biggest global networks."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-network-size-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Network Size</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers have the largest global provider networks:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Largest Global Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">1.5M+ healthcare providers and 39,000+ hospitals worldwide with extensive direct billing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏥</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Hospital Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Access to top hospitals globally with 35,000+ partner facilities and excellent direct billing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇺🇸</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best US Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Deepest US provider network through Aetna's domestic connections.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇪🇺</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best European Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong European presence with extensive EU provider partnerships.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="why-network-matters">Why Network Size Matters</h2>
  <p>
    A large provider network affects your insurance experience:
  </p>

  <h3>More Choices</h3>
  <p>
    Large networks provide flexibility:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>More doctors and hospitals to choose from</li>
    <li>Better chance of finding English-speaking providers</li>
    <li>More specialists in your area</li>
    <li>Options if you don't like first choice</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Better Direct Billing</h3>
  <p>
    Network size correlates with direct billing:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>More network hospitals means more direct billing</li>
    <li>Pay less out-of-pocket upfront</li>
    <li>Fewer claims to file</li>
    <li>Simpler healthcare experience</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Quality Assurance</h3>
  <p>
    Network hospitals are vetted:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Insurers evaluate quality before adding to network</li>
    <li>Network hospitals meet minimum standards</li>
    <li>Easier to trust care quality</li>
    <li>Problems with providers are tracked</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Access More Providers"
    description="Compare insurers by network size and direct billing coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Network Size Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Largest Global Network</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global has built the largest international provider network.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>1.5M+ healthcare providers globally</li>
    <li>39,000+ partner hospitals</li>
    <li>Extensive direct billing network</li>
    <li>Strong presence on every continent</li>
    <li>Easy provider search in app</li>
    <li>Network includes top facilities</li>
    <li>Growing continuously</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Network strongest in major cities. Some rural areas have limited options. Still the broadest global coverage.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Excellent Hospital Network</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global focuses on quality hospital partnerships.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>1.2M+ providers globally</li>
    <li>35,000+ partner hospitals</li>
    <li>Focus on top-tier facilities</li>
    <li>Excellent direct billing network</li>
    <li>Strong quality standards</li>
    <li>Good coverage worldwide</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Slightly smaller than Cigna. Focus on quality over quantity. Excellent for those wanting best hospitals.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — Best US Network</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International leverages Aetna's US network.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Deepest US provider network</li>
    <li>Access to US specialists</li>
    <li>Good global coverage</li>
    <li>Strong in Americas</li>
    <li>Seamless US care access</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best if US coverage matters. Global network smaller than leaders. Excellent for US-connected expats.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h3>Allianz Care — Strong European Network</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care has deep European roots and partnerships.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Extensive European network</li>
    <li>Good direct billing in EU</li>
    <li>Strong local partnerships</li>
    <li>Growing global presence</li>
    <li>Good for Europe-based expats</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> European focus may limit other regions. Growing but smaller globally. Best for European expats.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our full Allianz Care review</a></p>

  <h2 id="network-by-region">Networks by Region</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={regionColumns} rows={regionRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>North America</h3>
  <p>
    The US has the most complex healthcare system:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Aetna has deepest US connections</li>
    <li>Cigna also strong in US</li>
    <li>Direct billing important given high US costs</li>
    <li>Network access affects out-of-pocket costs significantly</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Europe</h3>
  <p>
    Well-developed healthcare with good networks:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Allianz has strongest European network</li>
    <li>Cigna and Bupa also excellent</li>
    <li>Direct billing common in major cities</li>
    <li>Public healthcare supplements private insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Asia Pacific</h3>
  <p>
    Growing region with improving networks:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cigna and Bupa lead in Asia</li>
    <li>Strong networks in Singapore, Thailand, Hong Kong</li>
    <li>Growing presence in Southeast Asia</li>
    <li>Variable coverage in developing markets</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Middle East</h3>
  <p>
    Concentrated healthcare in Gulf states:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong networks in UAE, Saudi, Qatar</li>
    <li>Cigna and Bupa have good Gulf coverage</li>
    <li>Direct billing common in premium hospitals</li>
    <li>Quality facilities in major cities</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Check Your Region"
    description="Network strength varies by region—verify coverage where you'll be."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="direct-billing">Direct Billing Networks</h2>

  <h3>What Direct Billing Means</h3>
  <p>
    Direct billing (cashless) lets you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Receive care without paying upfront</li>
    <li>Hospital bills insurer directly</li>
    <li>You pay only deductible/copay</li>
    <li>No claims to file</li>
    <li>Available at network facilities</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Network vs Out-of-Network</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-network:</strong> Direct billing available, negotiated rates</li>
    <li><strong>Out-of-network:</strong> Pay and claim, may cost more</li>
    <li>Most plans cover both, but network is easier</li>
    <li>Larger network = more direct billing options</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Finding Network Providers</h3>
  <p>
    How to find in-network care:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use insurer's mobile app</li>
    <li>Search online provider directory</li>
    <li>Call 24/7 assistance line</li>
    <li>Ask at hospital if they're in network</li>
    <li>Request direct billing authorization before admission</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Does network size affect premium cost?</h3>
  <p>
    Larger networks typically come with higher premiums because maintaining partnerships costs money. However, the convenience of direct billing and more provider choices often justifies the cost, especially for frequent healthcare users.
  </p>

  <h3>What if there's no network provider near me?</h3>
  <p>
    You can use out-of-network providers—pay upfront and submit claims for reimbursement. Coverage still applies; it's just less convenient. Emergency care is always covered regardless of network status.
  </p>

  <h3>How do I verify a provider is in-network?</h3>
  <p>
    Use your insurer's provider search (app or website), call the provider directly and ask if they work with your insurer, or contact your insurer's customer service. Always verify before non-emergency care.
  </p>

  <h3>Are network numbers real or inflated?</h3>
  <p>
    Reported network sizes include all types of providers (doctors, clinics, hospitals, labs, pharmacies). Hospital counts are more meaningful for serious care. Check network presence in your specific location, not just global numbers.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I access any hospital in an emergency?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Emergencies are covered at any hospital. Go to nearest appropriate facility. Contact your insurer as soon as possible—they can often arrange direct billing even at non-network hospitals for emergencies.
  </p>

  <h3>Do budget insurers have smaller networks?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally yes. Budget insurers invest less in network development and maintenance. They may have adequate coverage in major cities but limited options elsewhere. Premium insurers have larger, better-maintained networks.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Network sizes are approximate and change over time. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify network coverage in your specific location before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
